    "updated_at": "2024-08-02T15:16:12Z",
    "body": "Just browsing through open issues and came across this one.. I can see that Rust has the necessary functionality to provide this, but I'm not a developer.. So, with that in mind, here is a work-around just in case you haven't come up with a solution already.\r\n\r\nYou can provide the interface info using a custom module. I've tested the following on MacOS and it works fine. \r\n```toml\r\n[custom.interface]\r\nformat = \"$symbol $output\"\r\ndescription = \"testing\"\r\nsymbol = '󰩠'\r\nwhen = true\r\ncommand = \"route get default | grep interface | awk '{print $2}'\" # MacOS\r\n# command = \"ip route get 1 | awk '{print $5; exit}'\" # Linux\r\n# command = \"netstat -rn | grep default | awk '{print $6}'\" # BSD\r\n```\r\n\r\nFirst line of my format:\r\n```toml\r\n[╭─](fg:#FFFFFF)[ $os ${custom.interface} $localip](fg:#3B76F0 bg:#FFFFFF)[](fg:#FFFFFF bg:#3B76F0)\r\n```\r\n\r\nFont Used:\r\nMeslo v3.2.1 (MesloLGMDZ Nerd Font)\r\n\r\nHere's how it looks for me in MacOS and Ubuntu, using Bash configured with a transient prompt:\r\n\r\n## MacOS Screenshot\r\n<img width=\"1080\" alt=\"macos-starship-custom-interface-transient-bash\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bad6b1d9-dc13-4ad3-be9a-8ad572ddaae9\">\r\n\r\n## Ubuntu Screenshot\r\n![ubuntu-starship-custom-interface-transient-bash](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b294d6c0-cb11-49a6-8c8e-ccf9b81ce790)\r\n",
