    "body": "The command pulls the current active gateway so it “may” work fine,\r\nregardless of which VPN you are connected to. Try it out and report back 😉\r\n\r\nBurke Azbill\r\n\r\n\r\nOn Fri, Aug 2, 2024 at 11:16 AM Burke Azbill ***@***.***>\r\nwrote:\r\n\r\n> Just browsing through open issues and came across this one.. I can see\r\n> that Rust has the necessary functionality to provide this, but I'm not a\r\n> developer.. So, with that in mind, here is a work-around just in case you\r\n> haven't come up with a solution already.\r\n>\r\n> You can provide the interface info using a custom module. I've tested the\r\n> following on MacOS and it works fine.\r\n>\r\n> [custom.interface]format = \"$symbol $output\"description = \"testing\"symbol = '󰩠'when = truecommand = \"route get default | grep interface | awk '{print $2}'\" # MacOS# command = \"ip route get 1 | awk '{print $5; exit}'\" # Linux# command = \"netstat -rn | grep default | awk '{print $6}'\" # BSD\r\n>\r\n> First line of my format:\r\n>\r\n> [╭─](fg:#FFFFFF)[ $os ${custom.interface} $localip](fg:#3B76F0 bg:#FFFFFF)[](fg:#FFFFFF bg:#3B76F0)\r\n>\r\n> Font Used:\r\n> Meslo v3.2.1 (MesloLGMDZ Nerd Font)\r\n>\r\n> Here's how it looks for me in MacOS and Ubuntu, using Bash configured with\r\n> a transient prompt:\r\n> MacOS Screenshot macos-starship-custom-interface-transient-bash.png (view\r\n> on web)\r\n> <https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bad6b1d9-dc13-4ad3-be9a-8ad572ddaae9> Ubuntu\r\n> Screenshot\r\n>\r\n> ubuntu-starship-custom-interface-transient-bash.png (view on web)\r\n> <https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b294d6c0-cb11-49a6-8c8e-ccf9b81ce790>\r\n>\r\n> —\r\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/starship/starship/issues/6004#issuecomment-2265625968>,\r\n> or unsubscribe\r\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/ABUGWGP3YWY6GVQV3YIJLTTZPOPFHAVCNFSM6AAAAABITCAHD2VHI2DSMVQWIX3LMV43OSLTON2WKQ3PNVWWK3TUHMZDENRVGYZDKOJWHA>\r\n> .\r\